Linux UAPI commit 602544773763 (kernel v6.18 cycle, 2026-01-13) promoted the
XFS aliases EFSBADCRC (== EBADMSG) and EFSCORRUPTED (== EUCLEAN) into
<asm-generic/errno.h>. systemd's errno-to-name.awk only skips the older
EDEADLOCK/EWOULDBLOCK/ENOTSUP aliases, so on headers carrying the new ones it
emits two designated initializers for index 74 and 117. With systemd's
unconditional -Werror=override-init that is a hard error. Extend the skip list
to match; a no-op on headers that predate the promotion. Remove once vcpkg's
systemd carries the upstream fix.

diff --git a/src/basic/errno-to-name.awk b/src/basic/errno-to-name.awk
--- a/src/basic/errno-to-name.awk
+++ b/src/basic/errno-to-name.awk
@@ -3,6 +3,6 @@
 BEGIN{
         print "static const char* const errno_names[] = { "
 }
-!/(EDEADLOCK|EWOULDBLOCK|ENOTSUP)/ {
+!/(EDEADLOCK|EWOULDBLOCK|ENOTSUP|EFSBADCRC|EFSCORRUPTED)/ {
         printf "        [%s] = \"%s\",\n", $1, $1
 }
